posts.post_title: Tough T, E, and M cards, inc. T207, Obaks, Pet Cigs. - Make an offer!
posts.post_content:
Posted By: Brian C.
It's 10 cent dump day on ebay, so I'll have a "make an offer" day.

RARE OBAKS
Phil Cooney (Jewish), 1911 Obak, SGC 60 (SGC's highest graded example; 1/1)
Anson Mott, 1909 Obak, SGC 50 (none graded higher by SGC)
Terry McKune, 1909 Obak, SGC 40 (just 1 graded higher by SGC)

OTHER OBAKS
1911 John Bassey. SGC 40. SGC has graded only two examples higher.
1911 Ike Butler. SGC 30. SGC has graded only two examples higher.
1910 Jack Fournier. SGC 20. Tough "Clean - Wholesome" back.
1910 Mickey LaLonge. SGC 40. SGC has graded only two examples higher.
1910 Danny Shea. SGC 20. Gilliam Squires stamp on back.
1910 Fred Weed. SGC 20. Gilliam Squires stamp on back.
1911 Jimmy Shinn. SGC 40. Printer's proof mark at the top center; see below.
1910 Feliz Martinke. SGC 30.
1911 Harry Spencer. SGC 30. 
1910 Danny Shea. SGC 20.

T207
John Adams, SGC 50 (highest SGC-graded Adams; 1/1, a VERY tough card), Anonymous back. Factory 3.
Vean Gregg, SGC 40 (highest SGC-graded Gregg; 1/1), Anonymous back. Factory 3.
Buddy Ryan, SGC 50 (just 2 graded higher by SGC), Broadleaf back.
Walter Kuhn, SGC authentic (super tough; low pop.), Broadleaf back.
Larry McLean, SGC 60 (just 4 graded higher by SGC), Recruit back.

MISCELLANEOUS BASEBALL
Dick Breen, Imperial Tobacco (1912), SGC 40 (only 1 graded higher by SGC).
T210 (1910) Rose, SGC 10 (super tough; this is the only one graded by SGC).
Danny Shay, E91A (1908), SGC 40 (none graded higher by SGC).
Jack Graney, M101-4(1916), SGC 30 (just one graded higher by SGC).
Walter Ruether, Yeunglings (1928), SGC 40 (this is the only one graded by SGC).

BOXING
T229 Pet Cigarettes Abe Atell (SGC 30) and Monte Attell (SGC 10). Cross collectible for Jewish collectors, Black Sox collectors, boxing collectors, and T229 collectors.
